Hey, thanks for all the good feedback! To be honest, I think that the second-person perspective is getting to me more than the prose, I already have problems with run-on sentences and some of my favourite transitions no longer flowing well seem to exacerbate it. As to the standard operating procedure bit, I have an explanation there in my updated lore doc. Stealth is hard in space, so the military does a first, mostly random search through a percentage of systems for any signs of intelligent, space-faring life under the justification that anything that could catch up to a human ship has FTL, in turn meaning that they also likely have a presence in a bunch of systems. Then, given the prohibitive costs of doing a full search over everything for profitable rings, belts, terraformable rocks, etc. as a military op they auction off the job of surveying sections to the lowest bidder, who then come back and gets a cash bonus for any especially good finds.
